(20, 'How The CS:GO Ranking System Works!', 'csgo rank system.jpg', 'CSGO (Counter-Strike: Global Offensive) has a competitive mode that allows players to compete against each other to see who ranks the highest. The ranking system in CSGO is a way of determining the skill level of players based on their performance in matches. The CSGO ranking system uses a complex algorithm that takes into account a player\'s wins, losses, and the skill level of their opponents to assign them a rank. There are a total of 18 ranks in the CSGO competitive mode, ranging from Silver I to Global Elite.\r\n\r\nIn CSGO, the ranking system works by using a modified version of the Glicko-2 rating system. This system takes into account not only wins and losses but also the strength of the opponent and the certainty of the rating. This means that players will be matched with opponents of similar skill levels, and the more matches they win, the higher their rank will be.\r\n\r\nThe ranking system is based on an Elo rating system, which is a mathematical system that is used to calculate the relative skill levels of players in competitive games. The Elo system takes into account the results of each match, the skill level of the opponents, and the strength of the team. The higher a player\'s Elo rating, the better their chances of winning against lower-rated opponents.\r\n\r\nWhen a player first starts playing in the competitive mode, they will need to play a set of placement matches to determine their initial rank. Once their rank has been determined, they will be matched against other players of similar skill levels. Players who win more matches will rank up, while players who lose more matches will rank down. However, if a player consistently performs well, they will be able to rank up faster than players who perform poorly.\r\n\r\nOverall, the CSGO ranking system is designed to ensure that players are matched with opponents of similar skill levels. This allows players to enjoy the game and compete in a fair and balanced environment. With a range of ranks to work towards, players are motivated to improve their skills and climb the ranks to reach the highest levels of the competitive mode.', 'Harun picture.jpg', 'Harun Pasuli', NULL, '2023-03-07 18:25:23', 'Gaming', NULL),
(22, 'Why You Should Play Dauntless!', 'dauntless-monster-hunting-game-fig1-776918.jpg', 'Dauntless is an action-packed role-playing game that offers an exciting adventure for players looking to explore a world of epic creatures and challenging battles. Here are five reasons why you should consider playing Dauntless.\r\n\r\nFirstly, Dauntless offers a unique gameplay experience where players can team up with other Slayers to hunt down fearsome Behemoths. These Behemoths are colossal creatures that possess unique abilities and weaknesses, offering a diverse range of combat encounters that require different tactics and strategies. With a variety of weapons and skills at your disposal, you can customize your playstyle and take on these beasts in an action-packed battle.\r\n\r\nSecondly, Dauntless has a rich and engaging storyline that follows the journey of the player character as they seek to become the ultimate Slayer. Along the way, players will discover new locations, meet interesting characters, and uncover the secrets of the Shattered Isles. The game\'s lore is deep and immersive, offering an experience that goes beyond just fighting Behemoths.\r\n\r\nThirdly, Dauntless is a free-to-play game that is accessible to everyone. Unlike other games that require a large investment upfront, Dauntless offers a low barrier to entry, allowing players to jump in and start playing without any cost. The game also has a variety of microtransactions that allow players to purchase cosmetic items and other optional features, but these do not provide any significant advantage in gameplay.\r\n\r\nFourthly, Dauntless has a vibrant and welcoming community that offers a supportive and engaging environment for players. The game\'s developers have created a space where players can connect with each other, share tips and strategies, and even form guilds and clans. This community aspect adds a layer of social interaction to the game, making it an enjoyable and rewarding experience.\r\n\r\nLastly, Dauntless is constantly evolving, with new updates and content being added regularly. The game\'s developers are committed to providing players with a fresh and engaging experience, and this commitment is reflected in the frequent updates and events that keep the game exciting and dynamic. Whether you\'re a seasoned player or a newcomer, there\'s always something new to discover in the world of Dauntless.\r\n\r\nIn conclusion, Dauntless is a thrilling and engaging game that offers a unique experience for players looking for an action-packed adventure. With its diverse combat encounters, immersive storyline, accessible gameplay, supportive community, and constant updates, Dauntless is a game that is sure to provide hours of entertainment for players of all skill levels. So what are you waiting for? Join the hunt and become the ultimate Slayer in the world of Dauntless!', 'Harun picture.jpg', 'Harun Pasuli', NULL, '2023-03-22 18:25:16', 'Gaming', NULL),
(23, 'What Makes Albania\'s Flag So Special?', 'Flag_of_Albania.svg.png', 'During John Hunyadi\'s campaign in Niš in 1443, Skanderbeg and a few hundred Albanians defected from the Turkish ranks; for twenty-five years he scored remarkable victories against the Ottomans. He adopted the similar Byzantine imperial flag, with the double-headed eagle and the red background, and his victories brought him the papal title Athleta Christi.[5] The eagle was used for heraldic purposes in the Middle Ages by a number of noble families in Albania and became the symbol of the Albanians.[6] The Kastrioti\'s coat of arms, depicting a black double-headed eagle on a red field, became famous when he led a revolt against the Ottoman Empire resulting in the independence of Albania from 1443 to 1479. This was the flag of the League of Lezhë, which was the first unified Albanian state in the Middle Ages and the oldest representative political body in the country with extant records.\r\n\r\nThe symbol of the double-headed black eagle on a red background was re-used by Albanian nationalists during the 19th and early 20th centuries as a symbol of their campaign for their country\'s independence from the Ottoman Empire.[11][6][12] In Ottoman territory, the first time it was raised in possibly over 400 years is the Battle of Deçiq (6 April) in the Albanian revolt of 1911. It was raised by the rebellion leader Ded Gjo Luli on the peak of Bratila (present-day Tuzi Municipality) after victory was secured. The phrase Tash o vllazën do t’ju takojë të shihni atë që për 450 vjet se ka pa kush (Now brothers you have earned the right to see that which has been unseen for 450 years) has been attributed to Ded Gjo Luli by later memoirs of those who were present when he raised the flag.[13] It was one of three banners brought to Malësia by Palokë Traboini, student in Austria. The other two banners were used by Ujka of Gruda and Prelë Luca of Triepshi.[14]\r\n\r\n\r\nAlbanian flag on a pole at the entrance of Krujë Castle\r\nThe Albanian flag has gone through a number of changes over the years as different regimes have modified it. During the reign of King Zog (r. 1928–1939), a crown was added to the flag and was replaced by two fasces during the Italian occupation of Albania. After World War II, the communist regime added a five-pointed golden star, which was removed on 7 April 1992 after the communist government in Albania collapsed.\r\n\r\nAlbania\'s maritime flags—the civil ensign and the naval ensign—are both different from the national flag. The civil ensign consists of three horizontal bands of red, black, and red. The naval ensign is similar to the national flag, except that the eagle is on a white field, and the lower portion of the flag has a red stripe. The eagle of the flag of Albania is depicted on the reverse of the Albanian five lekë coin, issued in 1995 and 2000.[15]\r\n\r\nBeginning in 1969, the flag of Albania was widely unofficially flown in Kosovo by the country\'s ethnic Albanian population.[16] The flag was the symbol of the self-declared proto-state Republic of Kosova during the 1990s. Kosovo uses a different flag that was designed to avoid any symbols associated with a particular ethnic group, similarly to the flags of Bosnia and Herzegovina and Cyprus.', 'Harun picture.jpg', 'Harun Pasuli', NULL, '2023-03-08 18:25:39', 'Design', NULL),
(24, 'Why You Should Play Overwatch', 'maxresdefault.jpg', 'Overwatch is a popular team-based first-person shooter game developed by Blizzard Entertainment. The game was released in 2016 and has since gained a massive following, with millions of players worldwide. The game is set in a futuristic world where players take on the role of heroes who fight to protect the world from dangerous threats.\r\n\r\nThe game features a diverse cast of heroes, each with unique abilities and playstyles. Players can choose from a variety of heroes such as Tracer, a fast and agile hero who can blink and rewind time, or Reinhardt, a tank hero who can charge through enemies and protect his team with his shield. Each hero has their own strengths and weaknesses, making team composition and strategy crucial to winning matches.\r\n\r\nOverwatch is known for its high-quality graphics and polished gameplay mechanics. The game features various game modes such as Quick Play, Competitive Play, and Arcade, each with its own unique rules and objectives. The game also has a robust ranking system, which allows players to compete against others of similar skill levels and climb the ladder to higher ranks.\r\n\r\nOne of the most unique features of Overwatch is its emphasis on teamwork. Players must work together to achieve their objectives and defeat the enemy team. Communication is key, and players are encouraged to use voice chat to coordinate with their team. The game also rewards players for performing well in their role, such as healing teammates or protecting objectives, rather than simply focusing on getting kills.\r\n\r\nOverall, Overwatch is an engaging and immersive game that offers something for players of all skill levels. Its unique cast of heroes, polished gameplay mechanics, and emphasis on teamwork make it one of the most popular multiplayer games of all time. Whether you\'re a casual player looking for some quick fun or a competitive gamer looking to climb the ranks, Overwatch has something for everyone.', 'Harun picture.jpg', 'Harun Pasuli', NULL, '2023-03-08 18:25:29', 'Gaming', NULL),
